(Q1)When would you want to use a remote repository rather than keeping all your work local?
You would like to use remote repository rather than keeeping all your work local if you would like others to help you on the project or 
if there is more than one person working on the repository or if working on an open scource project

(Q2)Why might you want to always pull changes manually rather than having Git automatically stay up-to-date with your remote repository?
I would like to pull changes manually rather than having it , is that when i am not using my personal computer at home and i may be working on different computer some where else so is better I pull the changes when i am on my computer

(Q3)Describe the differences between forks, clones, and branches. When would you use one instead of another?

forks is used on the github page to kind of downolad the repository while clone is used on your local machine to download the repository and branches are based on the local repository on your system
-use forks on the github page
-use clone on your local machine
-use branch to implement a new feature

(Q4)What is the benefit of having a copy of the last known state of the remote stored locally?

having the last known state is important because some time when you will be working on a project and you are offline or the area the you are does not have an internet connection
it will be good to have the last state locally